This paper is about spoken language technologies and personal assistants, which are typically associated with natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The proposed system involves a neural retrieval based question answering system, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR) and NLP. The use of reinforcement learning to optimize the F1-score is also a common technique in machine learning (ML) and AI. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SD (Sound).
